\newpage
Recall the equilibrium equation for our class of symmetrical
   tensegrities:
    $$\left(z_{OB}+z_{OC}\right)\left(x_{OA}+x_{OD}\right)
     =\left(x_{OB}+x_{OC}\right)\left(z_{OA}+z_{OD}\right)$$

By simple sustituting of coordinates we get:
  $$(z_{B} + z_{C})(x_{A} + x_{D}) = (x_{B} + x_{C})(z_{A} + z_{D})$$
 where $z_{p}$ and $x_{p}$ are the $z$ and $x$ components of point $p$
 in our coordinate system centered at $O$.  
Now looking at each factor in turn:
\begin{eqnarray*}
z_{B} + z_{C} & = & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\left(\cos\phi+\sin\phi\right) - d
      + \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\left(\sin\phi-\cos\phi\right) - d = 
      \sqrt{2} \sin\phi - 2 d \nonumber\\
x_{A} + x_{D} & = & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}d\left(\sin\phi+\cos\phi\right)
      -\frac{1}{2}\left(\cos\phi-\sin\phi\right)^2 +
      \frac{1}{2}\left(\sin\phi+\cos\phi\right)^2
      +\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}d\left(\sin\phi-\cos\phi\right) \nonumber\\
              & = & 2 \cos\phi \sin\phi + \sqrt{2} d \sin\phi \nonumber\\
x_{B} + x_{C} & = & -\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}d\left(\sin\phi+\cos\phi\right)
     +\frac{1}{2}\left(\sin\phi-\cos\phi\right)^2
     -\frac{1}{2}\left(\sin\phi+\cos\phi\right)^2
     +\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}d\left(\sin\phi-\cos\phi\right) \nonumber\\
              & = & -2 \cos\phi \sin\phi - \sqrt{2} d \cos\phi \nonumber\\
z_{A} + z_{D} & = & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\left(\cos\phi+\sin\phi\right) - d
    + \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\left(\cos\phi-\sin\phi\right) - d = 
    \sqrt{2} \cos\phi - 2 d  \nonumber\\
\end{eqnarray*}
