Now we can set these factors equal to one another and solve for $d$.
$$
(\sqrt{2} \sin\phi - 2 d)(2 \cos\phi \sin\phi + \sqrt{2} d \sin\phi)
= (-2 \cos\phi \sin\phi - \sqrt{2} d \cos\phi)(\sqrt{2} \cos\phi - 2
d) $$
$$ \Longleftrightarrow
- \left(\sqrt{2} \cos\phi + \sqrt{2} \sin\phi\right) d^2
+ \left(1 - 4 \sin\phi \cos\phi\right) d 
+ \sqrt{2} \cos\phi \sin^2\phi + \sqrt{2} \sin\phi \cos^2\phi = 0 $$
Using the quadratic formula $\left[ax^2+bx+c=0 \Longrightarrow x =
 \frac{-b \pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\right]$ we get
\begin{eqnarray*}
d(\phi) & = & \frac{ 1 - 4 \cos\phi \sin\phi
\pm \sqrt{(1 - 4 \cos\phi \sin\phi)^2 + 4 (\sqrt{2} \cos^2\phi \sin\phi +
\sqrt{2} \sin^2\phi \cos\phi) (\sqrt{2} \sin\phi +
\sqrt{2} \cos\phi)}}{2 \sqrt{2}(\sin\phi + \cos\phi)} \\
        & = & \frac{ 1 - 4 \cos\phi \sin\phi\pm \sqrt{
32 \cos^2\phi \sin^2\phi + 1}}{2 \sqrt{2}(\sin\phi + \cos\phi)}
\end{eqnarray*}
The negative root can be shown to be absurd (its values for $d(\phi)$
are negative which is not possible in our model). 
